  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison apologizes for the delay in thanking Caroline C. Thayer for her note and accompanying gifts; Garrison was waiting until the enclosed volume of Garrison&apos;s writings was properly bound before sending his thanks. Garrison will highly prize the &quot;sculpted semblance&quot; of Theodore Parker. Garrison describes Theodore Parker as &quot;a brave hearted reformer of no common stature, who, though now popularly decried and rejected, is building for himself a most solid frame. May he long be preserved, perfecting himself in knowledge in grace, and mightily aiding in the redemption of an oppressed and suffering world!&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
